<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Well, I don't know about the rest of you, but this is my first wiki and I'm feeling rather embarassedly like the old person who's behind the times and scrambling to keep up. Nevertheless, I'm having fun pegging away at the Documentation and assorted other things, and I'd love to see more actual ToME gaming discussion here. So:  <p>
Just dive in and try it. The water's fine! :)  
</p>
<p>
<a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: The water seems too cold :p It has been fun to play around with the wiki and posting around. Meanwhile, I'm working on my own rogue-like *gasp* Yeah, I know. I might post a demo release soon. I'm working on light effects and perception improvements mostly. Ie. things have diferent settings of transparency, so you can actualy look into the woods a lil bit, dirty glass wont allow you to see as far as a clean glass will, if you see the thing out but can't guess what it is, it will appear as a ? instead of it's default symbol and so on. Eh, that's just me babbling about non-tome stuff. But if the tome guys want to use my ideas, go ahead. 
</p>
